I'll now retry the data_processing_validator with a basic default schema and the default input data path. Since the tool requires a schema, I'll provide a simple JSON schema that validates for any object structure.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "*": {
        "type": "any"
      }
    }
  },
  "data": "data/input.json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I see the validator is expecting XML format data. I'll modify the call to specify XML format in the options and use a basic XML schema for validation.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "xs:schema": {
      "xmlns:xs": "http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema",
      "xs:element": {
        "name": "root",
        "type": "xs:string"
      }
    }
  },
  "data": "data/input.xml",
  "options": {
    "format": "xml"
  }
}
</tool_call>

            Now that the validation step is complete, I'll proceed with the next step in the workflow: data transformation. I'll execute the data_processing_transformer tool with default parameters.

<tool_call>data_processing_transformer
{
  "input_format": "xml",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I notice the transformer has a dependency on data_processing_parser that needs to be executed first. I'll execute the parser tool before retrying the transformer.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "input": "data/input.xml",
  "format": "xml",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

I'll try using the file_operations_converter tool as an alternative to transform the XML data to JSON format, as it doesn't have the same parser dependency.

<tool_call>file_operations_converter
{
  "input_format": "xml",
  "output_format": "json",
  "options": {
    "input_file": "data/input.xml",
    "output_file": "data/output.json"
  }
}
</tool_call>
